    <titleStmt>
        <title>Dialogue Act Markup Language</title>
        <abbr>DiAML</abbr>
    </titleStmt>
    <scope>Markup language for dialogue annotation</scope>
    <keyword>dialogue</keyword>
    <keyword>semantic annotation</keyword>
    <keyword>markup language</keyword>
    <info type="description">
        <p>
            Dialogue Act Markup Language (DiAML) is defined within the ISO standard 24617-2 (Semantic Annotation Framework, Part 2: Dialogue Acts). 
            DiAML has a 3-part definition:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>an abstract syntax specifiying the possible annotation structures (i.e. elements of an annotation and how these elements may be combined),</li>
            <li>a formal semantics of the structure interpretation in abstract syntax, and</li>
            <li>a concrete syntax specifying an XML representation of the annotation structures.</li>
        </ol>
    </info>
